GitHub Copilot Chat Assistant — summary of issues fixed and refinements

Fixed incorrect dimension reporting (dim was non-virtual and base's dim() was used in exceptions).
Made dimension an explicit compile-time value (static constexpr Dim) and used it for error messages.
Replaced the custom exception with RangeException derived from std::out_of_range and improved the error message and stored fields.
Replaced int indices with std::size_t for safety and consistency.
Added const overloads for operator[].
Removed using namespace std from the header and made functions noexcept/constexpr where appropriate.
Removed the infinite while(1) in main and replaced with a normal return.
Improved formatting and modernized code to be safer and clearer.

Notes and suggestions

These changes keep the original template approach and interface but make behavior well-defined and safer.
If you plan to support runtime dynamic sizes, consider implementing a different container that uses std::vector and stores shape metadata.
Consider renaming begin()/end() to lower()/upper() to avoid confusion with iterator semantics, but I kept the original names for compatibility.
If you want to support iterators and range-based for, we can add begin()/end() iterator overloads in a follow-up.
